	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "He was the bishop of Constantinople and is regarded as the greatest preacher of the Greek Church. He lived a hermit life in the years  371-377. \n                     He was ordained  as a priest in  386 and then he preached in the Church of Antioch for 12 years. Then, in   397 he became the patriarch of Constantinople.\n                     He was an extraordinary writer whose works were also translated into Gǝʿǝz. \n                    \n                  " .
